President Trump signed a bill reaffirming the United States' commitment to NASA's core mission of human space exploration, space science, and technology. The bill supports ongoing medical monitoring and treatment for astronauts, as well as the transition of activities to the commercial sector. It also supports the commercial crew program, deep space exploration, and space science. The bill aims to ensure that the United States remains a leader in aviation and space flight. President Trump and the attending politicians praised NASA and its astronauts for their bravery and contributions to the country.